This place is gorgeous.
If you're a vlogger, photo addict. The place is so cinematic,  for a moment you'll forget that it's a car yard.
In fact, the vehicle background makes an appealing background.
Getting back to business. Some staff are helpful while some are total shit. My consultant was unavailable when l was there because l was too early for the appointment.
He asked for another colleague to assist me, and this particular guy did not care to assist. He was pretty annoyed. Kept me waiting for 30mins as he was busy making circles. Later, after speaking to a senior person, l was informed that he was acting like that because he basically has no commission if l was to go through with the purchase and l was also taking him away from potential customers. Still this attitude was inexcusable.
They have all cars for a vast array of price ranges. Your money determines.
I like that they tell you exactly what's wrong with the car. They fix all road worthy elements for "A" rated vehicles and that there is a 2 year repair warranty.
Basically, the teams who assist you. Your sales person, financial specialists are great. Kudos to Thuso and Christine for being great.

text.text:
I recently had the pleasure of selling my car at the Woodmead branch of We Buy Cars, and I must say, the experience was exceptional. From the moment I stepped into the dealership POD, I was greeted by a gentleman named CW, who went above and beyond to ensure my satisfaction throughout the entire process.

CW's professionalism and dedication to providing excellent customer service were evident from the start. He took the time to understand my needs and preferences, ensuring that I felt valued as a customer. He patiently answered all my questions and guided me through the entire selling process, making it seamless and hassle-free.

What truly set CW apart was his genuine concern for my satisfaction. Not only did he work tirelessly to secure a fair price for my car, but he also followed up with a phone call to check if I was happy with the sale. This level of personalized care is rare in the automotive industry, and I truly appreciate CW's commitment to going the extra mile.

The overall experience at the Woodmead We Buy Cars branch was fantastic. The staff was friendly, the facilities were clean and well-maintained, and the entire process was efficient and transparent. I felt confident that I was getting a fair deal, thanks to CW's expertise and attention to detail.

Based on my experience, I highly recommend the Woodmead We Buy Cars branch to anyone looking to sell their vehicle. Whether you're a first-time seller or have prior experience, CW and the team will ensure that you receive top-notch service, fair value for your car, and peace of mind throughout the process.

Thank you, CW, for your outstanding service and dedication. You have truly exceeded my expectations, and I will not hesitate to recommend Woodmead We Buy Cars.

I bought a car at We Buy Cars Dome branch. I've paid R3304 for the vehicle delivery and R2200 for licence and registration. I collected the vehicle myself, it was not delivered to me. The vehicle was not even ready when I fetched it because they were charging the battery just to get me out. I had to buy a new battery as well. I didn't receive a licensed and registered vehicle from them. I only received an email and a document I had to go and print. It was up to me to do everything for a service I've already paid for.
I demand all the money I have payed for that service and didn't receive. It's more than three months now and with various emails I only get promises and the middle finger.

text.text:
Poor customer service to assist in cancelling a deal
I purchased a vehicle from WBC The Dome branch and collected it on the 2nd of October 2024(Wednesday). The car started overheating way 20 min away from the Dome on my way home. This issue was not in the condition report provided by Dekra. I returned the vehicle the following day (3rd October - Thursday) to the branch. The Sales Consultant who assisted me took the car in for diagnosis.  I was then contacted by the head office on Saturday (5th October) asking whether I wanted them to fix the vehicle or cancel the deal, to which I communicated that I wanted to cancel the deal.

I followed up on Monday (7th October) with the Sales Consultant who told me that he is waiting for the workshop to do a diagnosis to be able to send to head office for them to make the cancellation. After being told the same story for 3 days I went to the branch on Thursday (10th October) and only then the manager escalated the issue. Even after sending the diagnosis report required by the head office to make the cancellation, I am told I must wait another 3 to 5 days for them to process the cancellation.

So WBC expects me to wait for 2 weeks or even a month on a vehicle that is financed under my name earning interest to wait for their internal processes to cancel a vehicle sitting at their workshop!!!! Every single person from the consultant, manager, dealer principles, head office, the whole entire team does not want to take accountability to assist me.

text.text:
I bought my car from the We Buy Cars at The Dome branch, to date I still don’t have a valid car disc and have raised numerous complaints on their website and via the sales agent that assisted me.

I’ve been pulled over by traffic officials so many times due to this, this is putting me at a huge risk in the event of an accident, getting unnecessary fines, etc. I’ve fought with them on multiple occasions to get temporary permit which are only valid for a period of 3 weeks.

Every-time I call their office and sales agent, I get nowhere but more frustrated and they tell me it’s not them but the company that was handling all Natis applications (which honestly is not my problem as they are contracted to them). This is honestly so frustrating and stressful.

This is a total bad customer experience and I wouldn’t recommend them to anyone. They are happy to take your money and the moment you leave their doors , you’re just a distant memory not worth their service.

I brought a megan 2018 Gline in Pietermaritzburg on the 21th of August just before my mothers birthday wanted to suprise her I traveled all the way from stilfontain to PMB I was with my brother did everything by the book took the car for test drive I was happy took it home to Newcastle but when we traveled from KZN the to stilfontain 23rd of August the car gave a reading "engine failure hazard" which I immediately call the sales person and told him about it.

The following day I had to drop it off at germiston workshop and I stayed there for a week and they paid 5k to fix it. I later collected it thinking everything was fine boom 1 day driving this car same problem took it back again this time it will cost 70k to fix it I was heartbroken.
I had to cancel the deal on the 27th of September mind you all this time the car is at the workshop I haven't really enjoyed driving it.end if September my car insurance and monthly installment went through even after canceling the deal.i didn't even have the vehicle in my possession the person who is assisting me told me the was nothing they can do about my installment, so basically paid for nothing no car nothing.i have called so many times requesting my cancelation latter or proof that the deal is off nothing It been 4 weeks now and am afraid I will be dedicated money again this month. What hurts most this car was a platinum car the best of the best the derka report indicated nothing was wrong with the car.
I won't advise anyone to buy a car from webuycars I had and still going through the most worse experience of my life.I don't understand why is it so hard to cancel the deal I call I send emails I even know my reference number by head now.Buying my first car was suppose to be the most happiest time of my life instead I got the worse experience eva.
Platinum,Gold,Green there all the same nothing specially about it.
Am so angry and disappointed I feel let down I have been crying at work am unable to do my job am depressed 😔 ☹️ 🙁 😢 😥 .and Noone calls me I have to be the one that calls every week is the feedback and get the same answer which is No .
